ed sample\nleads to results similar to that of the fiducial sample, with slightly stronger\nredshift dependence of the normalisation ($\\zeta\\simeq 0.5$) and weaker\nredshift dependence of the slope (${\\rm d} \\beta/{\\rm d} \\log (1+z)\\simeq\n0.18$) when $\\beta$ varies with time. At $z=2$ ETGs with $M_*\\approx\n10^{11}\\,M_\\odot$ have, on average, $\\approx1.7$ higher $\\sigma_\\mathrm{e}$\nthan ETGs of similar stellar mass at $z=0$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Oct 2019 18:14:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 Jul 2020 16:11:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-12"}
