nce in weakly interacting\nsystems with periods within the same range. The latter is thought to be\nevidence of a capture in the 3:2 mean motion resonance of the two binaries.\nThis sets important constraints on evolutionary channels in these systems. The\ntotal number of doubly eclipsing systems increased to 146, more than 90% of\nwhich are at low declinations on the southern sky.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Oct 2019 00:29:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-17"}
