ispersion relations\nare discussed. However, in view of the fact that the transition form factors\nare complex quantities, the current data situation does not allow for a full\ndetermination of the subtraction constants. To reduce the number of free\nparameters, unsubtracted dispersion relations are used to make predictions for\nthe transition form factors in the low-energy space- and timelike regions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Oct 2019 15:02:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-22"}
